what is database
A database is an organized collection of structured information, or data, typically stored electronically in a computer system

Your grocery store, bank, restaurant, online shopping sites, hospital, favorite clothing store and mobile service provider, for instance all use databases to keep track of customer, inventory, employee and accounting information
it is easy to store data with database
Databases allow for data to be stored quickly and easily and are used in many aspects of your daily life

database is managed by dbms
dbms stands for database management system
now a days..dbms are used everywhere.for example school,banking,hospital,etc.
